This paper deals with the problem of human pose estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture that uses multiple stages and cross-stage feature aggregation, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its approach on the COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark for object detection and segmentation, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of multi-person pose estimation, which involves tracking multiple individuals in an image, making cs.RO (Robotics) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
